00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,710
I've always been curious.

289
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:40,200
Why are these pottery figurines black?

290
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,120
The cracks, the eyes, the noses.

291
00:14:42,300 --> 00:14:43,630
All the holes are black.

292
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,120
Right.

293
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:44,910
Even the butt cracks

294
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:45,510
are black.

295
00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:46,340
What?

296
00:14:46,630 --> 00:14:47,100
Butt cracks...

297
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:48,160
Alright, alright.

298
00:14:48,310 --> 00:14:49,640
If it had a black glaze,

299
00:14:50,770 --> 00:14:52,410
it wouldn't be so densely coated.

300
00:14:52,410 --> 00:14:54,340
It wouldn't get into all the holes.

301
00:14:55,410 --> 00:14:56,690
That's why I suspected

302
00:14:57,810 --> 00:14:59,270
it might have been burned.

303
00:15:01,090 --> 00:15:03,130
So they were burned,

304
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:03,990
but why are only the male figurines

305
00:15:03,990 --> 00:15:05,390
dated to the Western Jin?

306
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:07,790
Shouldn't they all be dated
to the Western Jin?

307
00:15:07,790 --> 00:15:08,820
Did you notice?

308
00:15:08,850 --> 00:15:09,900
The male figurines

309
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:11,870
are all black.

310
00:15:12,290 --> 00:15:15,020
And the black color penetrates deep
into the clay

311
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:16,580
and evenly distributed.

312
00:15:16,830 --> 00:15:18,030
The female figurines

313
00:15:18,050 --> 00:15:19,140
are not that black,

314
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:21,490
and the color isn't evenly distributed.

315
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:22,770
I think I know.

316
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:23,750
I think

317
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,260
the male figurines

318
00:15:25,340 --> 00:15:27,000
were closer to the fire
when they were burned.

319
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,460
Like the grilled potatoes.

320
00:15:28,460 --> 00:15:29,910
Black and shiny.

321
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,070
The female figurines

322
00:15:31,070 --> 00:15:32,340
were further from the fire.

323
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:33,690
Like smoked chicken.

324
00:15:34,130 --> 00:15:36,530
Being far away,
they were burned unevenly.

325
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:39,190
I think you should stop with archaeology
and start roasting chicken.

326
00:15:39,190 --> 00:15:40,850
Isn't it a vivid description?

327
00:15:41,310 --> 00:15:43,440
You really get it when it comes to food.

328
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:46,100
So what are you looking for?

329
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:48,500
I read a document before.

330
00:15:49,030 --> 00:15:51,890
It said tomb robbery was rampant
during the Wei and Jin periods.

331
00:15:51,890 --> 00:15:53,710
Tomb raiders robbed the emperor mausoleum.

332
00:15:53,710 --> 00:15:54,380
I suspect

333
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,840
the fire was caused by those tomb raiders.

334
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:57,900
If we can figure out

335
00:15:57,910 --> 00:16:00,040
which emperor mausoleum they robbed,

336
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:01,640
we might be able to

337
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:03,990
